      "email",
      {
        "html": "<p>We're currently working on additional reports on the Silicon Valley Bank collapse. In the meantime, check out <a href=\"__GHOST_URL__/campaign-cash-goes-in-late-fees-come-out/?utm_source=newsletter-email&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=newsletter-article\">today’s featured story</a> below on how a group of House Republicans is attacking efforts to limit the excessive credit card late fees that plague consumers, particularly those in low-income and majority Black neighborhoods. Why might they be doing so? As we note, the hundreds of thousands of dollars credit card companies have funneled to these politicians might have something to do with it.</p>"
      }
